Syria Fires Tear Gas to Disperse Mourners at Daraa, BBC Says

-- B y   M a r i a m   F a m
-- 
2011-03-19T16:06:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-19/syria-fires-tear-gas-to-disperse-mourners-at-daraa-bbc-says.html
Syrian security forces fired tear
gas to disperse crowds chanting anti-government slogans at the
funeral of two people killed during protests yesterday, the
 British Broadcasting Corp . said today, citing witnesses.  At least one mourner was arrested at the funeral in the
southern border town of Daraa, the  BBC  said on its website,
citing rights activists. The Syrian state news agency Sana
reported yesterday that “infiltrators”  attacked security
forces.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mariam Fam in Cairo at 
 mfam1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 